OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FBank boss says UK interest 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Frate cut 'on the way'      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, The Bank of England boss has said "we  
OL,6, are on the way" to interest rate cuts  
OL,7, after they were left unchanged at      
OL,8, 5.25%, their highest for 16 years.     
OL,10,FThe Bank still needed to see inflation 
OL,11,Ffall further, but last month's drop to 
OL,12,F3.4% was "very encouraging and good    
OL,13,Fnews," governor Andrew Bailey said.    
OL,15,FBut he said rate cuts could come before
OL,16,Finflation hits its 2% target.          
OL,18,FIt leaves open the option that the Bank
OL,19,Fcould cut interest rates as early as   
OL,20,FMay, sooner than had been expected.    
